Exercise 10.3

Part(b)

autocorrelation_1 = function(b){b/(1+b^2)}
curve(autocorrelation_1, from=-5, to=5, , xlab="b", ylab="autocorrelation(b) (t=1)")

Part(c)

epsilon <- rnorm(n=500,mean=0,sd=1)
X1 = c()
X2 = c()
for(t in 1:500){
  X1[t] = epsilon[t+1]+0.5*epsilon[t]
  X2[t] = epsilon[t+1]-0.5*epsilon[t]
}

plot(1:500, X1)

plot(1:500, X2)
